  "text": "The collagen sponge honeycomb (AteloCell ○ R ; 9mm in diameter, 2mm in thickness, Koken Co.,Ltd, Japan) was composed of a collagen membrane, 1m in thickness, that had smooth surfaces. The sponge had parallel pores, 200-400m in diameter, with a honeycomb structure extending from the top to the bottom. The surface of the collagen sponge was coated with the MWCNTs by the method described previously [CITATION_1] . The MWCNT-coated sponge was observed by scanning electron microscopy (Hitachi S-4000, Japan) and transmission electron microscopy (Hitachi H-800, Japan).",
